<item>
            <title>[LU-12911] Setting a LOV EA can access or change outside allocated buffer</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12911</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The attribute passed to ll_setstripe_ea() is copied to a buffer allocated&#160; based on size information passed from userspace.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But the contents of this attribute are analyized and possibly changed (in ll_adjust_lum) &lt;b&gt;before&lt;/b&gt; the size is validated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can result in a warning from KASAN, and could result in memory corruption.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The size should be validated before, or while, the attribute is examined.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
